HRSA primary care content skip header and navigation H R S A News Brief http www hhs gov U S Department of Health Human Services Health Resources and Services Administration HRSA NEWS ROOM http newsroom hrsa gov http newsroom hrsa gov November 05 2003 Contact HRSA Press Office 301 443 3376 HHS Names New Members to Primary Care Advisory Committee HHS Secretary Tommy G Thompson has announced the appointment of eight health care professionals to serve on the Advisory Committee on Training in Primary Care Medicine and Dentistry The committee counsels the Secretary and Congress on a wide range of policy and program issues in family medicine internal medicine pediatrics dentistry and physician assistant programs Joining the 23 member advisory committee for two year terms are Margaret I Aguwa D O M P H professor and chair of family and community medicine Michigan State University East Lansing Mich David P Asprey Ph D P A C associate professor Physician Assistant Program University of Iowa Iowa City Iowa Tammy L Born D O owner and chief medical officer Born Preventive Health Care Clinic Grand Rapids Mich Rudolfo R Burquez D D S general dentist Whittier Calif Tina Lee Cheng M D M P H chief of general pediatrics and adolescent medicine Johns Hopkins University Baltimore Md Warren A Heffron M D professor of family and community medicine University of New Mexico Albuquerque N M Man Wai Ng D D S M P H pediatric dentist Children s National Medical Center Washington D C and Eugene C Rich M D professor and chair of medicine Creighton University Omaha Neb HHS Health Resources and Services Administration and its Bureau of Health Professions provide staff support to the committee which meets three times a year For more information on the committee visit http bhpr hrsa gov medicine dentistry actpcmd http bhpr hrsa gov medicine dentistry actpcmd Go to http newsroom hrsa gov H R S A News Room HRSA News Room http www hrsa gov H R S A HRSA http www hhs gov H H S HHS http www hrsa gov 508ac